xwikidoc.title: Konqueror
xwikidoc.content:
{{info}} Konqeror does not provide a complete file system like abstraction to a WebDAV share. {{/info}}
Konqueror is the default web browser in a KDE environment. It has much more capabilities than an ordinary web browser; WebDAV support is just one of them. In my own experience Konqueror's WebDAV support is quite superior to what is provided by Nautilus on a Gnome environment. The following steps demonstrate how to setup Konqueror to access XWiki WebDAV shares:
* Open Konqueror (either from the panel or from the KDE menu) and navigate to **Go -> Network Folders**: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@network.folders.png]]
* The next window lists all the network folders available for you. Double click on the **Add Network Folder** icon: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@new.connection.png]]
* On the next dialog, select **WebFolder(webdav)** as the network folder type and click **Next**: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@connection.type.png]]
* Now enter your connection settings and click **Save & Connect**: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@settings.png]]
* On the next window, fill in your authentication details for the remote XWiki server and click **Ok**: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@authenticate.png]]
* Now wait until Konqueror opens up your XWiki: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@browse.png]]
* That's it! If you go back to the **Network Folders** window of Konqueror you will see your new connection listed there: [[image:Features.WebDAVKonqeror@link.png]]
